[1mkernel[m
You can install the ISO kernel (fast and easy), set up a custom kernel
(recommended), or both (best of both worlds). Whatever you choose, you must
install at least one kernel.

For instructions on how to install the ISO kernel, type [1mtodo iso-kernel[m.

For instructions on how to install a custom kernel, type [1mtodo compile-kernel[m.

To see the instructions for this step again, just type [1mtodo[m.

When you are finished, type [1mnext[m.
